{{short description|生物学观察发现癌症发病率与生物细胞数量无关}}

{{Orphan|time=2021-02-11T13:24:03+00:00}}
'''佩托悖论'''（{{lang-en|Peto's paradox}}）指在[[物种|物种]]水平上，[[癌症|癌症]]的发生率似乎与生物体中的细胞数量无关。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Cancer and ageing in mice and men|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_british-journal-of-cancer_1975-10_32_4/page/411|first1=R.|last2=Roe|first2=F. J. C.|date=October 1975|journal=British Journal of Cancer|issue=4|doi=10.1038/bjc.1975.242|volume=32|pages=411–426|pmc=2024769|pmid=1212409|last3=Lee|first3=P. N.|last4=Levy|first4=L.|last5=Clack|first5=J.|last1=Peto}}</ref>例如，尽管[[鲸|鲸鱼]]的细胞数量多于[[人类|人类]]，但人类的癌症发病率却远远高于鲸鱼<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Why don't all whales have cancer? A novel hypothesis resolving Peto's paradox|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_integrative-and-comparative-biology_2007-08_47_2/page/317|first1=John D.|last2=Victor|first2=Erin M.|journal=Integrative and Comparative Biology|issue=2|doi=10.1093/icb/icm062|year=2007|volume=47|pages=317–328|pmid=21672841|last3=Cropper|first3=Jenese H.|last1=Nagy|doi-access=free}}</ref>。如果整个[[细胞|细胞]]致癌的概率是恒定的，那么鲸鱼的癌症发病率应当高於人类。英国统计学家和[[流行病学|流行病学]]家{{le|理查德·佩托|Richard Peto}}首先观察到了这种现象。

== 历史 ==
理查德·佩托在1977年首次提出了这个悖论：<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The real war on cancer: the evolutionary dynamics of cancer suppression|last=Nunney|first=Richard|date=January 2013|journal=Evolutionary Applications|issue=1|doi=10.1111/eva.12018|volume=6|pages=11–19|pmc=3567467|pmid=23396311}}<!--http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3567467/#b45--></ref>在一篇关于癌症多阶段模型的综述中，他指出，在细胞对细胞的基础上，人类比小鼠更不容易得癌症。另外，他还指出，不同物种间单个细胞致癌率不同的原因可能由于进化。

== 在同一物种间的体现 ==
在同一物种的中，即使控制了其他风险因素，患癌症的风险和体型也呈正相关。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Peto's Paradox: Evolution's Prescription for Cancer Prevention|last=Caulin|first=Aleah|last2=Maley|first2=Carlo|date=April 2011|journal=Trends in Ecology and Evolution|issue=4|doi=10.1016/j.tree.2011.01.002|volume=26|pages=175–182|pmc=3060950|pmid=21296451}}</ref>

1998年发表的一项对17,738名英国男性[[公務員|公务员]]进行的25年纵向研究显示，即使在控制了[[吸菸|吸烟]]等风险因素后，身高与[[癌症|癌症]]发病率之间也存在正相关，且具有高度的统计学可信度。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Height and mortality from cancer among men: prospective observational study|last=Smith|first=George|last2=Shipley|first2=Martin|date=14 November 1998|journal=BMJ|issue=7169|doi=10.1136/bmj.317.7169.1351|volume=317|pages=1351–1352|pmc=28717|pmid=9812932}}</ref>2011年一项针对100多万英国女性的类似研究发现，即使在控制了一些社会经济和行为风险因素后，也有强有力的[[统计学|统计]]证据表明癌症与身高之间存在关系。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Height and cancer incidence in the Million Women Study: prospective cohort, and meta-analysis of prospective studies of height and total cancer risk|author=Jane Green|date=August 2011|journal=Lancet Oncology|issue=8|doi=10.1016/S1470-2045(11)70154-1|volume=12|pages=785–794|pmc=3148429|pmid=21782509|author3=Delphine Casabonne|author4=F Lucy Wright|author5=Gillian Reeves|author6=Valerie Beral|author7=Million Women Study collaborators|author2=Benjamin J Cairns}}</ref>2011年对74,556只北美家养狗的死因分析发现，小型犬种的癌症发病率最低，证实了先前的研究结果。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Mortality in North American Dogs from 1984 to 2004: An Investigation into Age-, Size-, and Breed-Related Causes of Death|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/27c2ebbc18a5698ad6cb849fa346f354795cd5ab|last=Fleming|first=J.M.|last2=Creevy|first2=K.E.|date=25 February 2011|journal=Journal of Veterinary Internal Medicine|issue=2|doi=10.1111/j.1939-1676.2011.0695.x|volume=25|pages=187–198|pmid=21352376|doi-access=free}}</ref>

== 在不同物种间的体现 ==
然而，在不同物种之间，这种相关性就不复存在。<ref>{{Cite web|title=how-big-animals-deter-cance|url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/how-big-animals-deter-cancer/|accessdate=2021-02-10|author=|date=|format=|work=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2018-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620080110/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/how-big-animals-deter-cancer/}}</ref>2015年，在[[圣迭戈动物园|圣地亚哥动物园]]的一项研究，选取了从51克的[[条纹松鼠|条纹草鼠]]到4,800公斤的[[大象|大象]]，共计36种不同的[[哺乳類动物|哺乳類动物]]，体型大了近10万倍。研究发现体型与癌症发病率之间没有关系，为佩托最初的观察提供了经验支持。<ref>{{citation|last=Schiffman|first=Joshua|date=8 October 2015|title=Potential Mechanisms for Cancer Resistance in Elephants and Comparative Cellular Response to DNA Damage in Humans|journal=JAMA|volume=314|issue=17|pages=1850–60|doi=10.1001/jama.2015.13134|pmid=26447779|pmc=4858328}}</ref>

== 进化因素 ==
研究发现多细胞生物的起源于癌症之间存在联系，证实生物进化为[[多細胞生物|多细胞生物]]需要抑制[[癌症|癌症]]的发生。<ref name=":2">{{Cite journal|title=Peto's Paradox: Evolution's prescription for cancer prevention|first1=A. F.|last2=Maley|first2=C. C.|journal=Trends in Ecology & Evolution|issue=4|doi=10.1016/j.tree.2011.01.002|year=2011|volume=26|pages=175–182|pmc=3060950|pmid=21296451|last1=Caulin}}</ref>随着生物体的体系变大、寿命变长，生物体需要更强大的癌症抑制能力。<ref name=":3">{{cite journal|title=Acquired multicellular-mediated resistance to alkylating agents in cancer|first1=H|last2=Man|first2=S|date=15 April 1993|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America|issue=8|doi=10.1073/pnas.90.8.3294|volume=90|pages=3294–8|bibcode=1993PNAS...90.3294K|pmc=46286|pmid=8475071|last1=Kobayashi}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{cite journal|title=Phylostratigraphic tracking of cancer genes suggests a link to the emergence of multicellularity in metazoa|first1=Tomislav|last2=Tautz|first2=Diethard|date=21 May 2010|journal=BMC Biology|issue=66|doi=10.1186/1741-7007-8-66|volume=8|pages=66|pmc=2880965|pmid=20492640|last1=Domazet-Lošo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=https://www.nature.com/news/massive-animals-may-hold-secrets-of-cancer-suppression-1.12258|url=https://www.nature.com/news/massive-animals-may-hold-secrets-of-cancer-suppression-1.12258|accessdate=2021-02-10|author=|date=|format=|work=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2021-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210216220438/https://www.nature.com/news/massive-animals-may-hold-secrets-of-cancer-suppression-1.12258}}</ref>有证据表明，大象、蓝鲸等大型生物具有更强的抵抗癌症的能力。<ref name=":5">{{cite journal|title=Links between metabolism and cancer|last=Dang|first=Chi|date=2012|journal=Genes & Development|issue=9|doi=10.1101/gad.189365.112|volume=26|pages=877–90|pmc=3347786|pmid=22549953}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Massive animals may hold secrets of cancer suppression|url=http://www.nature.com/news/massive-animals-may-hold-secrets-of-cancer-suppression-1.12258|last=Gewin|first=Virginia|journal=Nature News|doi=10.1038/nature.2013.12258|language=en|access-date=2021-02-10|archive-date=2019-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190429000405/http://www.nature.com/news/massive-animals-may-hold-secrets-of-cancer-suppression-1.12258}}</ref>而中等大小的生物，虽然缺少相关的抵抗癌症的基因，但由于更强的生育能力，依旧能够使物种延续。<ref name="Nature">{{cite journal|title=Massive animals may hold secrets of cancer suppression|url=http://www.nature.com/news/massive-animals-may-hold-secrets-of-cancer-suppression-1.12258|last=Gewin|first=Virginia|date=21 January 2013|journal=[[Nature_News|Nature News]]|accessdate=12 March 2014|doi=10.1038/nature.2013.12258|archive-date=2019-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190429000405/http://www.nature.com/news/massive-animals-may-hold-secrets-of-cancer-suppression-1.12258}}</ref>

不同物种已经进化出各不相同的抑制癌症的机制。<ref name=":6">{{cite news|last=Zimmer|first=Carl|date=October 8, 2015|title=Elephants: Large, Long-Living and Less Prone to Cancer|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/13/science/why-elephants-get-less-cancer.html|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|access-date=October 13, 2015|archive-date=2019-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808164229/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/13/science/why-elephants-get-less-cancer.html}}</ref>2015年1月，《细胞报告》上的一篇论文声称在弓头鲸（Balaena mysticetus）中发现了可能与长寿有关的基因。<ref name=":7">{{cite journal|title=Insights into the Evolution of Longevity from the Bowhead Whale Genome|first1=Michael|last2=Semeiks|first2=Jeremy|date=6 January 2015|journal=Cell Reports|issue=1|doi=10.1016/j.celrep.2014.12.008|volume=10|pages=112–122|pmc=4536333|pmid=25565328|last3=Webb|first3=Andrew E.|last4=Li|first4=Yang I.|last5=Quesada|first5=Víctor|last6=Craig|first6=Thomas|last7=Madsen|first7=Lone Bruhn|last8=van Dam|first8=Sipko|last9=Brawand|first9=David|last26=López-Otín|last24=Suydam|last25=Larsen|first24=Robert|first26=Carlos|first30=João Pedro|last27=O’Connell|first28=John W.|first10=Patrícia I.|last29=Thomsen|last28=Bickham|first29=Bo|last30=de Magalhães|last23=George|first23=J. Craig|last1=Keane|first22=John C.|last15=Grishin|last10=Marques|first25=Knud|first16=Nynne Hjort|last11=Michalak|last17=Heide-Jørgensen|first12=Lin|last13=Bhak|first13=Jong|last14=Yim|first14=Hyung-Soon|first15=Nick V.|last22=Patton|last16=Nielsen|first11=Pawel|first27=Mary J.|first17=Mads Peter|first18=Elias M.|last19=Matson|first19=Cole W.|last20=Church|first20=George M.|last21=Stuart|first21=Gary W.|last12=Kang|last18=Oziolor}}</ref>几乎同一时间，另一个研究小组在[[裸鼹鼠|裸鼹鼠]]中发现了一种[[多糖|多糖]]，似乎可以阻止[[贅生物|肿瘤]]的发展。2015年10月，两项独立的研究表明，大象的基因组中有20个肿瘤抑制基因TP53，而人类和其他[[哺乳动物|哺乳动物]]只有一个。<ref name=":8">{{cite journal|title=How elephants avoid cancer: Pachyderms have extra copies of a key tumour-fighting gene.|last=Callaway|first=E.|date=8 October 2015|journal=Nature|doi=10.1038/nature.2015.18534|volume=526}}</ref>其他研究显示，在保存下来的[[猛犸象|猛犸象]]DNA中存在14个这种基因，但在大象最亲近的活体亲戚[[海牛目|海牛]]和[[鬣狗科|鬣狗]]的DNA中只有一个。这些结果表明，正如佩托所理论的那样，动物体型与肿瘤抑制之间存在进化关系。

== 新陳代谢与细胞大小的因素 ==
2014年Maciak和Michalak在《进化应用》上发表的一篇论文强调了「细胞大小与不同物种之间的代谢和细胞分裂率的关系在很大程度上没有得到重视」，认为这是造成这個悖论的关键因素，并得出结论：「较大的生物体有更大的、分裂缓慢的细胞，能量周转率更低，这都能显著降低癌症的起病风险。」<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Cell size and cancer: A new solution to Peto's paradox?|first1=S.|last2=Michalak|first2=P.|journal=Evolutionary Applications|issue=1|doi=10.1111/eva.12228|year=2015|volume=8|pages=2–8|pmc=4310577|pmid=25667599|last1=MacIak}}<!-- http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/eva.12228/abstract --></ref>

Maciak和Michalak认为，细胞大小在哺乳類动物物种间并不统一，使得身体大小并不能完全表明细胞数量。（例如，大象单个[[红血球|红血球]]的体积大约是[[欧鼩鼱|欧鼩鼱]]的四倍。）<ref>{{cite web|title=Mammal erythrocyte sizes|url=http://www.genomesize.com/cellsize/mammals.htm|date=2004-02-03|last=Gregory|first=T. Ryan|website=Genome Size|access-date=13 October 2015|archive-date=2016-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160528170432/http://www.genomesize.com/cellsize/mammals.htm}}</ref>此外，较大的细胞相比较小的细胞分裂得更慢，这种差异在生物体的生命周期内呈指数级增长。较少的细胞分裂意味着较少的癌症突变机会，而癌症发病率的数学模型对[[细胞分裂|细胞分裂率]]高度敏感。<ref>{{cite journal|title=A simple algebraic cancer equation: calculating how cancers may arise with normal mutation rates|last=Calabrese|first=Peter|last2=Shibata|first2=Darryl|date=5 January 2010|journal=BMC Cancer|issue=3|doi=10.1186/1471-2407-10-3|volume=10|pages=3|pmc=2829925|pmid=20051132}}</ref>此外，较大的动物一般具有较低的[[基础代谢率|基础代谢率]]，遵循一个明确的[[反对数|反对数]]关系。因此，它们的细胞随着时间的推移，每单位体重所造成的损伤会更小。这些因素结合起来，可以解释这一悖论。

